    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Comedy at Woody Point - Stacey McGunnigle, Chris Wilson & Adam Christie"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Comedy returns to Woody Point for its 11<sup>th</sup> year, hosted by Steve Patterson, with a lineup of nationally recognized talent and award-winning performers.</p>\n\n<p>Friday night brings a sharp, fast-paced showcase featuring Stacey McGunnigle and Chris Wilson of This Hour Has 22 Minutes, alongside Juno Award-winning comedian Adam Christie, whose material blends personal storytelling with unexpected turns into absurdity.</p>\n\n<p>Saturday night continues with another set from Christie, joined by returning favourite James Mullinger, known for his high-energy, crowd-charged performances. Both evenings feature musical guests, the Louis McDonald Trio, adding a live soundtrack to the weekend.</p>\n\n<p>Across two nights, the festival offers a mix of award-winning comedy, recognizable voices, and a lively, intimate atmosphere.</p>\n\n<p>The event is presented by Writers at Woody Point with presenting sponsor Pike's Service Station and Trucking </p>\n\n<p>Find more information: <a href='http://www.writersatwoodypoint.com/' target='_blank'>www.writersatwoodypoint.com</a></p>\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n.location-event-temp {display: none!important;}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
