    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Music Monday - Catherine MacLellan"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Catherine MacLellan has been captivating audiences around the world with her music for over two decades. Born and raised in the idyllic province of Prince Edward Island, Catherine's songs reflect her deep connection to the land and the people that call it home. Her passion for songwriting runs in the family; her father, Gene MacLellan, wrote beloved hits like 'Snowbird' and 'Put Your Hand in the Hand.'</p>\n\n<p>While Catherine's music is rooted in folk and roots, her sound has evolved to embrace a wider range of influences over the course of her 7 albums. From heart-wrenching ballads to uplifting anthems, her music has a universal appeal that speaks to the struggles, triumphs, and joys of life.</p>\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {\n    display: block!important;\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
